      "message": "Missing validation for empty IPv4 grid scenario\n\nCurrent Code:\n```\n${ipv4_elems}\u003d  Get WebElements  ${ipv4_addr_origin_elements}\n${ipv4_origin_list}\u003d  Get IP Origins  @{ipv4_elems}\n```\nIssue: The keyword doesn\u0027t validate whether any IPv4 addresses exist in the grid before checking origin uniqueness. If the grid is empty (no IPv4 addresses configured), Get WebElements returns an empty list, and the test would pass even though it hasn\u0027t validated the actual constraint.\n\nFix: Add validation to ensure at least one IPv4 address exists before checking origin uniqueness:\n\n```\n${ipv4_elems}\u003d  Get WebElements  ${ipv4_addr_origin_elements}\n${elem_count}\u003d  Get Length  ${ipv4_elems}\nShould Be True  ${elem_count} \u003e 0\n...  msg\u003dNo IPv4 addresses found in grid. At least one IPv4 address must be configured to verify origin uniqueness.\n${ipv4_origin_list}\u003d  Get IP Origins  @{ipv4_elems}\n```\n\nWhy: From a network configuration perspective, the test should validate the constraint only when IPv4 addresses are actually configured. An empty grid is a different state that should be explicitly handled or documented.",
