      "message": "No verification of DHCP property state after toggle\n\nCurrent Code:\n```\n# Toggle the DHCP property.\nToggle DHCPv4 Property And Verify  ${property}  ${xpath_property}\nWait Until Element Is Not Visible  ${xpath_page_loading_progress_bar}  timeout\u003d60s\n```\n\nIssue: The keyword relies entirely on Toggle DHCPv4 Property And Verify to handle the toggle operation, but doesn\u0027t independently verify the final state of the DHCP property. If the toggle operation fails silently or the property reverts, the test would still pass as long as the gateway remains unchanged.\n\nFix: Add explicit verification of the DHCP property state after toggle:\n```\n\n# Get initial DHCP property state\n${initial_state}\u003d  Get Element Attribute  ${xpath_property}  checked\n\n# Toggle the DHCP property.\nToggle DHCPv4 Property And Verify  ${property}  ${xpath_property}\nWait Until Element Is Not Visible  ${xpath_page_loading_progress_bar}  timeout\u003d60s\n\n# Verify property state actually changed\n${final_state}\u003d  Get Element Attribute  ${xpath_property}  checked\nShould Not Be Equal  ${initial_state}  ${final_state}\n...  msg\u003dDHCP property ${property} did not toggle as expected.\n```\n\nWhy: From a GUI testing perspective, verifying the actual state change ensures the toggle operation succeeded. This is critical for network configuration where a failed toggle could leave the system in an inconsistent state.",
      "revId": "ce433c36e1aead471a2b20c9007d88efd65a4001",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
